{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"dailP0MR8nIVqoelobEaN","title":"Linear_Algebra","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"basic-definitions":{"type":"header","text":"Basic Definitions","value":"basic-definitions","line":8,"column":0},"square-matrices":{"type":"header","text":"Square Matrices","value":"square-matrices","line":11,"column":0},"positive-definite-matrices":{"type":"header","text":"Positive Definite Matrices","value":"positive-definite-matrices","line":22,"column":0},"matrix-decompositions":{"type":"header","text":"Matrix Decompositions","value":"matrix-decompositions","line":29,"column":0},"eigenvalues-and-eigenvectors":{"type":"header","text":"Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors","value":"eigenvalues-and-eigenvectors","line":31,"column":0},"singular-value-decomposition":{"type":"header","text":"Singular Value Decomposition","value":"singular-value-decomposition","line":36,"column":0},"principal-components-analysis":{"type":"header","text":"Principal Components Analysis","value":"principal-components-analysis","line":46,"column":0},"matrix-differentiation":{"type":"header","text":"Matrix Differentiation","value":"matrix-differentiation","line":63,"column":0},"kronecker-products":{"type":"header","text":"Kronecker Products","value":"kronecker-products","line":65,"column":0},"other-results":{"type":"header","text":"Other Results","value":"other-results","line":70,"column":0}},"fname":"Appendix.Linear_Algebra","updated":1636343740473,"created":1635165273731,"parent":"CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"60644798c03564ee52c97623ae863f1f","custom":{}},"body":"<h2 id=\"basic-definitions\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#basic-definitions\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Basic Definitions</h2>\n<h2 id=\"square-matrices\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#square-matrices\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Square Matrices</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>trace(A)</li>\n<li>diag(A)</li>\n<li>trace(AB) = trace(BA)</li>\n<li>|A| = det(A)</li>\n<li>|AB| = |A||B|</li>\n<li></li>\n<li></li>\n<li></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"positive-definite-matrices\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#positive-definite-matrices\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Positive Definite Matrices</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>A</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>></mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x'Ax > 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.790992em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>B</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>></mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B'AB > 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.790992em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span> if <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span></span> is of full column rank</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>></mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A^{-1} > 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.853208em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">rank(A) = p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"matrix-decompositions\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#matrix-decompositions\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Matrix Decompositions</h2>\n<h3 id=\"eigenvalues-and-eigenvectors\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#eigenvalues-and-eigenvectors\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors</h3>\n<p>Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors are only defined for square matrices. </p>\n<p>The no. of non zero eigenvalues corresponds to the rank of the matrix.</p>\n<h3 id=\"singular-value-decomposition\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#singular-value-decomposition\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Singular Value Decomposition</h3>\n<p>The generalisation of eigendecompositions to rectangular (non square) matrices.</p>\n<p>Typically not used in the factor literature too much, and more so in the machine learning literature.</p>\n<p>For our purposes, it can be shown that an SVD of a square matrix is equivalent to an eigendecomposition. </p>\n<p>That is, the left and right matrices as given by an SVD will be identical and correspond to the eigenvectors, and the middle </p>\n<h2 id=\"principal-components-analysis\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#principal-components-analysis\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Principal Components Analysis</h2>\n<p>The principal components are typically calculated by running an eigendecomposition on the variance matrix of some dataset. Normally, datasets are X = N x p with N much larger than p, and so this done via <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>N</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1/(N - 1)(X'X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>However, this is not always the case in macroeconomic data, which instead has the data structure X = T x N, where T and N are of similar dimensions (although typically <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>></mo><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T > N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.72243em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi><mo>></mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N > T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.72243em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span> when quarterly/yearly data is used). In accordance with Bai and Ng's review chapter on DFMs, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">XX'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the \"tilde\" normalization, and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X'X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span> is the \"bar\" normalisation. In the literature, both are used depending on the model setup (one can be easier to work with than the other), but the \"tilde\" nroamlisation tends to be more common.</p>\n<p>Note that in R, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X'X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span> is the same as crossprod(), and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><msup><mi>X</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">XX'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the same as tcrossprod(). The former options are preferred for readability in general, even though they are slightly slower.</p>\n<p>In terms of saving on computational costs, whichever option which results in a covariance matrix of smaller dimensions is preferred, though asymptotically the theoretical results for either are the same.</p>\n<p>It should be noted that there is a lack of sign identification for the eigenvectors - each eigenvector is observationally equivalent to its negative. The eigenvalues themselves are not affected by this. For this reason, it is helpful and common to fix the signs, typically such that the first element of each eigenvector is positive. This is what the current implementation does by default.</p>\n<p>Although eigen() is the traditional backend, the algorithm behind this is considered to be numerically unstable and a bit outdated, particularly when there is very high multicollinearity. As such, the machine learning community tends to prefer using SVD on the covariance matrix instead of eigen, as this tends to be numerically more stable and faster. SVD is a generalisation of eigen for rectangular matrices, and can be shownt o be identical when the matrix is symmetric (covariance matrix).</p>\n<p>princomp() is usually the implementation preferred, as this provides an OOP interface with other useful methods, such as projecting new data using the decomposition. However, these extra features are typically not needed in macroeconomic analysis, so a much simpler interface using just eigen() or svd() is used instead.</p>\n<h2 id=\"matrix-differentiation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#matrix-differentiation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Matrix Differentiation</h2>\n<h2 id=\"kronecker-products\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#kronecker-products\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Kronecker Products</h2>\n<h2 id=\"other-results\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#other-results\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Other Results</h2>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":451},"end":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":462},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":464},"end":{"line":14,"column":12,"offset":475},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Meeting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"TODO","alias":"TODO","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":477},"end":{"line":16,"column":9,"offset":485},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"TODO"}}],"anchors":{"quick-links":{"type":"header","text":"Quick Links","value":"quick-links","line":17,"column":0},"to-do-list":{"type":"header","text":"To do List","value":"to-do-list","line":25,"column":0}},"fname":"root","updated":1636683885086,"created":1595961348801,"parent":null,"children":["CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","9s2d4L1UHWFWCdtORYT2Q","AiXOWFsdvi3BPZxcUMjIi","MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","MXHvc8bQbNRRVCB0UogRy","T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","jtZSk246bVVDfJy6cdpS1","2qGHFR7CcKOE0Meu7UU6D","qGmGYptDKW2WLwlsu2xJw","GvwoAWaYZxq1czYi3t3k4","ZIDZSAYP9a9L7jYhVMgcz","WOnXV41UlGcOQzEoTZzJU","fhf7Gdr3mhOUG1mU5twC6","AOvKFmg0tBcGmUASXaALX","qDVp6IFHf6FiUdSgxwZMA","fHzGITjWkNNkiwsQpdex4","umGHrdI4OaLoU8OOAOdkL","aQw5xJBpqunSJYCfXXAls","0R61RLuT7e3hswR2v6o0w","AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR","ElqQePaEuSSz7pSeO1gNc","BMClpTRP3V8ITqM7R4kh0","1ruiVSk3lFpEOUNqPnYti","FNflnQbSXuMwTtni2C8is","y0rpX1u3Lz3vpUFro9TcW"],"data":{},"contentHash":"d7de26282e04813f39247a66c191dd07","custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"body":"\nWelcome to my website!\n\nThis website has been built using Dendron, and each topic has been collated into collapsible sections on the left hand side. Below is a high level overview showing how each section is connected for ease of navigation.\n\n\n\nDendron has incredibly powerful search functionality due to good indexing, even outside of working in raw .md files. Simply use the search bar at the top of the website to find something.\n\n## Quick Links\n\n[[roadmap]]\n\n[[Meeting]]\n\n[[TODO]]\n\n## To do List\n\nType up Bai and Ng assumptions\n\nInvestigate Bates et al Assumptions\n\nInvestigate consistency of using an estimated break point in conjunction with BNIC\nThis seems to be consistent using k_tilde that itself may be Op(1)\n\nFix up BP test for better interface (low priority)\n\nImplement simulated Andrews exp and mean Wald/LM tests\n\n- look into RSpectra package (supposedly faster eigen)\n- not sure whether to rename this to SFM or not (lots of legacy code that needs to be changed)\n\nData\nFix and clean data for \n- AUMD (on hold, need to find date index)\n- FREDQD\n- CANMD (should be straightforward)\n- CANQD\n- UKMD (should be straightforward)\n\nInvestigate further sources of time series that could be used during COVID\n\nImplement truly dynamic factor models (Forni) using Dynamic PCA\n- BIG task\n- read into dynamic PCA\n- read into testing no. of dynamic factors\n- do not believe there is a literature focusing on breaks in the dynamic setup\n- implement dynamic PCA\n- implement testing no of factors, (look into ICshocks functions and make this interface better)\n- implement testing no of factors using AW test\n\nImplement BKW standard test (non sequential)\n\nFix up BKW test\n- implement a general plot method which plots *something* on the y axis, but most importantly, date on the x axis with estimated break dates, and each partition labelled with the no. of factors as determined by some consistent estimator\n\nFix up BE test\n- so that there is a consistent interface for accessing this\n\n\n\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":3,"useFMTitle":false,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"noLegacyNoteRef":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"usePrettyRefs":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","usePrettyRefs":true,"title":"Ze Yu","description":"Personal knowledge space","siteLastModified":true,"gh_edit_branch":"main","duplicateNoteBehavior":{"action":"useVault","payload":["vault"]},"siteUrl":"https://zeyuz35.github.io/","usePrettyLinks":true,"siteNotesDir":"notes","siteFaviconPath":"favicon.ico","gh_edit_link":true,"gh_edit_link_text":"Edit this page on GitHub","gh_root":"docs/","gh_edit_view_mode":"edit","writeStubs":true,"siteIndex":"root"},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTrace":false}},"randomNote":{},"insertNote":{"initialValue":"templates"},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","e